- Is this village really unaffected by the Cullings? [if Variables.get_var("unaffected") == false]
	Shopkeeper: Sure is. Not a single death, ever since they started occurring all those years ago. [do Variables.mod_var("questions", 1)][do Variables.set_var("unaffected", true)]
	Shopkeeper: The sky does turn red in the morning, heralding a Culling day, and we've had people die just outside our walls. 
	Shopkeeper: Gruesome, horrific way to go. Glad I've only witnessed it this one time.
	Shopkeeper: But inside, nothing. Not once. The Goddess cares for and protects us.
	- How is this possible?
