	Shopkeeper: The gist of it is, we get visions from the Goddess from time to time, and we can see more than other people can. 
	Shopkeeper: You'll see. => questions2
- Who are the "Elders"? [if Variables.get_var("elders") == false]
	Shopkeeper: They're the founders and leaders of our wonderful village and church. [do Variables.mod_var("questions", 1)][do Variables.set_var("elders", true)]
	Shopkeeper: There's 5 of them, and they're the only ones who can communicate directly with the Goddess, besides me, of course. 
	Shopkeeper: They're very old, hence the name. They rarely come out of their home. They have underlings and messengers in their service, and that's how they usually communicate the Goddess's will and teachings to us.
	Shopkeeper: There's a chance you won't ever see them yourself, but it's safer to assume they're aware of your every move. 
	Shopkeeper: They don't take kindly to meddling newcomers. And they're not known for being forgiving to heretics and blasphemers. 
	Shopkeeper: Since you're not technically part of our church yet, the most severe form of punishment you could undergo is exile. 
	Shopkeeper: But once you take the oath and become a fully fledged member, the punishment for sinning is either flogging, or death, depending on the severity of your actions. 
	Shopkeeper: Sounds worse than it is. All you have to do is not speak against or openly defy our Goddess. 
	- Sounds simple enough. => questions2
